<HEADLINE>
Glue To Melt Paper Onto Sheet Metal?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> "Will" &lt;westes-...@noemail.nospam&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-02-27T03:50:00 </POSTDATE>
I have an anti-tamper label that I want to glue onto the seal between two
halves of a metal enclosure.   I would appreciate specific product
recommendations for a glue that would meet these requirements.   Assume the
enclosure is made of galvanized sheet metal and the anti-tamper label is
made of a porous paper such as that used for paper currency.

- The glue must "melt" the paper onto the metal such that it is impossible
to remove the paper without completely destroying it.

- The glue must not deform or alter the coloration of the galvanized sheet
metal.

- The paper must be completely removable using a solvent, without damage to
the underlying sheet metal.

Can someone recommend specific manufacturers and products for this
application?

--
Will
